Alternative forms[edit]

  • sepultūrā afficiō

Etymology[edit]

sepultūra (“burial, interment”) + adficiō (“affect”)

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /se.pulˈtuː.raː atˈfi.ki.oː/, [sɛ.pʊɫ̪ˈt̪uː.raː at̪ˈfɪ.ki.oː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /se.pulˈtu.ra atˈfi.t͡ʃi.o/, [sɛ.pul̪ˈt̪uː.ra at̪ˈfiː.t͡ʃi.ɔ]

Verb[edit]

sepultūrā adficiō (present infinitive sepultūrā adficere, perfect active sepultūrā adfēcī, supine sepultūrā adfectum); third conjugation iō-variant

  1. Alternative form of sepultūrā afficiō
